National Security Advisor Jake Sullivan held a meeting with the national security advisors of France, Germany, Italy, and the United Kingdom at the White House. They expressed their commitment to supporting Ukraine in its defense against Russian aggression and aiding in its reconstruction. They also discussed holding Russia accountable for the damage caused in Ukraine and emphasized the importance of restoring constitutional order in Niger. Other topics of discussion included the Indo-Pacific region, the Middle East, and the upcoming G20 Leaders' Summit in New Delhi, India. The participants expressed their support for India's G20 Presidency and emphasized the need for strong outcomes at the summit.